# Security

## Secrets
- No secrets in code. All from env vars or secret manager.
- `.env` gitignored. `.env.example` committed with placeholders.
- API keys prefixed: `pk_` (public/frontend), `sk_` (secret/backend).

## Input validation
- Validate at boundaries: route handlers, WebSocket handlers, SDK init.
- Pydantic models for all incoming backend data. No raw dict access.
- Sanitize user strings before DOM rendering (prevent XSS). Reject payloads > 1MB.

## Auth
- Every request needs a valid API key. No anonymous access.
- `pk_`: read-only, rate-limited, frontend-safe. `sk_`: full access, server-side only.
- Validate keys via middleware. Cache lookups (5 min TTL). Scope all queries to authenticated `app_id`.

## Dependencies
- `npm audit` / `pip audit` in CI. Block high/critical vulns. Pin versions. Review before adding.

## Data privacy
- No PII at INFO+. Session data scoped per-user per-app. Row-level security in PostgreSQL.
- SDK never captures: keystroke content, passwords, screen recordings, clipboard, off-page browser content.
